'''类精神分裂型人格障碍'''（{{lang-en|schizoid personality disorder}}，缩写为[[SPD|SPD]]），又称'''类精神分裂人格违常'''、'''類分裂性人格疾患'''或'''孤僻型人格障礙症'''，是一种[[人格障礙|人格障礙]]，其特征在于对社会联系缺乏兴趣，倾向于独立生活、沉默寡言和感情淡漠。受影响者可能无法和他人形成健康的依赖关系，也可能会描绘出丰富的[[幻想_(心理學)|幻想世界]]。<ref>Authur S. Reber- Dictionary of Psychology, Penguin p.690 (1995)</ref>

與[[精神分裂症|精神分裂症]]並無關連，但共病性高，如[[疏离|疏离]]与{{link-en|感情迟钝|Blunted affect}}等。此外，精神分裂症家庭中SPD更常见。<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.pchtreatment.com/schizoid-personality-disorder-clinic.php |title = Schizoid Personality Disorder |last = Ball |first = Jeff |publisher = Psychological Care & Healing Treatment Center |accessdate = 2010-12-18 |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20101229210025/http://www.pchtreatment.com/schizoid-personality-disorder-clinic.php |archivedate = 2010-12-29 }}</ref>

一些心理学家争论類精神分裂型人格違常的定义由于[[文化偏见|文化偏见]]而具有缺陷：“分裂性人格者被[[医疗化|医疗化]]的原因之一是因为他们相对数量少。占人口大多数的普罗大众倾向于假设自己的心理状况[[正常|正常]]并将差异等同于病态”。因此“所谓的分裂人格只是[[美国心理学协会|美国心理学协会]]将正常人类差别病态化的又一公开例证。”<ref>Psychoanalytic Diagnosis, Second Edition: Understanding Personality Structure in the Clinical Process (Nancy McWilliams): [http://books.google.com/books?id=BzPOAWB2DncC&pg=PA196&lpg=PA196&dq=Schizoid+pathologizing&source=bl&ots=Sk0PXXdVjv&sig=8jCJ1gOEfpUzEtVD8jXTdUebkUk&hl=en&ei=GEuYTsyNIsz3sgay4IydBA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&sqi=2&ved=0CB8Q6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=Schizoid%20pathologizing&f=false] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=BzPOAWB2DncC&pg=PA196&lpg=PA196&dq=Schizoid+pathologizing&source=bl&ots=Sk0PXXdVjv&sig=8jCJ1gOEfpUzEtVD8jXTdUebkUk&hl=en&ei=GEuYTsyNIsz3sgay4IydBA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&sqi=2&ved=0CB8Q6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=Schizoid%20pathologizing&f=false |date=20140425061117 }}</ref><ref>Personality Disorders Are Not Illnesses (Philip Hickey PhD) [http://behaviorismandmentalhealth.com/2010/05/05/personality-disorders-are-not-illnesses/] {{Wayback|url=http://behaviorismandmentalhealth.com/2010/05/05/personality-disorders-are-not-illnesses/ |date=20100531020124 }}</ref><ref>A Giant Step Backward for Introverts (Nancy Ancowitz) [http://www.psychologytoday.com/blog/self-promotion-introverts/201008/giant-step-backward-introverts]</ref>

== 迹象和症状 ==
具有分裂人格的人通常对人疏远而冷漠，造成人际交往的困难。大多数被诊断为SPD的人都有建立个人关系和情感表达方面的缺陷，有可能在令人不快的处境里表现得十分[[被动|被动]]，与人交流简短而冷淡。由于缺乏有意义的交往，SPD患者通常不能发展出与其他人相处好坏程度的准确自我评估。<ref name="D. Laing- p.82-100">R. D. Laing- 'The Divided Self' chapter-5 'The Inner Self of the Schizoid Condition' p.82-100</ref>

这种评估被认为对人的自我认知、评判个人行为在社交场景中所造成影响的能力是非常重要的。{{link-en|R.D. Laing|R. D. Laing}}提出“不被注入人际现实，人的自我形象就会日益空虚并蒸发掉，最后导致不真实感。”<ref name="D. Laing- p.82-100" />

当个人空间被侵犯，分裂人格者会有窒息感，并感到有使自己从中解脱获得独立的必要。如果分裂人格者的伴侣感情[[亲密|亲密]]需要很少，他们会感到很轻松。有人提出，分裂人格者想躲避的不是人，而是正面或负面的情感、[[亲密感|亲密感]]和{{link-en|自我表露|Self-disclosure}}。<ref>Philip Manfield- 'Split Self, Split Object' p. 207</ref>

这意味着分裂人格者有可能与他人建立基于智力、身体、家庭、职业或娱乐活动等的人际关系，只要这种关系不要求或强迫其产生亲密感。[[唐纳德·威尼科特|唐纳德·威尼科特]]对这种调节人际关系的需要解释为分裂人格者“会按自己的喜好而不是他人的一举一动进行人际交往”。如果无法达到这点，他们则宁愿独处。<ref>D.W. Winnicott- p.73 'The Family and Individual Development' (1965)</ref>

尽管有人认为分裂人格者自鸣得意，也不注意他们自己的感受，许多人格分裂者还是能认识到自己和别人不一样的地方。一些治疗中的人格分裂者感受到生活离他们而去，或者自己生活在贝壳之中。他们像是错过了班车，在一个遥远的视角观察生活。<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.de/books?id=zlFVfzH8orMC&pg=PA236#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=Restructuring Personality Disorders: A Short-Term Dynamic Approach|last=Jeffrey J. Magnavita|first=|publisher=The Guilford Press|year=1997|isbn=1-57230-185-6|location=New York|pages=237|access-date=2017-10-06|archive-date=2017-09-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170927113517/https://books.google.de/books?id=zlFVfzH8orMC&pg=PA236#v=onepage&q&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=":5">{{Cite book|title=Integrated Treatment for Co-Occurring Disorders: Personality Disorders and Addiction|last=Sharon C. Ekleberry|publisher=Routledge|year=2008|isbn=978-0789036933|pages=31–32|chapter=Cluster A - Schizoid Personality Disorder and Substance Use Disorders|chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=O5HY1xcfjEcC&pg=PA31|access-date=2020-11-05|archive-date=2021-02-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210225085235/https://books.google.com/books?id=O5HY1xcfjEcC&pg=PA31|dead-url=no}}</ref> [[亞倫·貝克|亞倫·貝克]]和Freeman认为，分裂人格者认为他们是生活的观察者，而不是参与者。<ref name="beckfreeman">{{cite book|title=Cognitive Therapy of Personality Disorders|first=|publisher=The Guilford Press|year=1990|isbn=9780898624342|edition=1st|location=|pages=|quote=|via=|author=[[亞倫·貝克|Aaron T. Beck]], Arthur Freeman}}</ref>

分裂人格者倾向于将人格的单一功能分成几个部分。所以，分裂人格者的所思所为之间没有太多明显的联系。结果就是，他自己身体接触外界时产生的情感会大大减少。
<ref name="Lowen1994">{{tsl|en|Alexander Lowen||Alexander Lowen}} (1994). ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=yrA6Yu24NVYC Bioenergetics]''. Penguin/Arkana. {{ISBN|978-0-14-019471-5}}. ''The Schizoid Character Structure (p.151)''</ref>

人们也观察到，分裂人格和创造力也有关联。<ref>{{cite journal|last=David Schuldberg|date=|year=2001|title=Six subclinical spectrum traits in normal creativity|url=http://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1207/S15326934CRJ1301_2|journal=Creativity Research Journal|volume=13|issue=1|pages=5–16|doi=10.1207/s15326934crj1301_2|via=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=George Domino|date=|year=2002|title=Creativity and Ego Defense Mechanisms: Some Exploratory Empirical Evidence|url=http://dx.doi.org/10.1207/S15326934CRJ1401_2|journal=Creativity Research Journal|volume=14|issue=1|pages=17–25|doi=10.1207/S15326934CRJ1401_2|via=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Kinney|first=Dennis K.|last2=Richards|first2=Ruth|date=2001|year=|title=Creativity in Offspring of Schizophrenic and Control Parents: An Adoption Study|url=https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Dennis_Kinney/publication/233244470_Creativity_in_Offspring_of_Schizophrenic_and_Control_Parents_An_Adoption_Study/links/558b376008ae31beb1004844.pdf|journal=Creativity Research Journal|volume=13|issue=1|pages=17–25|doi=10.1207/S15326934CRJ1301_3|via=|access-date=2017-10-06|archive-date=2017-10-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171020180522/https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Dennis_Kinney/publication/233244470_Creativity_in_Offspring_of_Schizophrenic_and_Control_Parents_An_Adoption_Study/links/558b376008ae31beb1004844.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 隐秘的分裂人格者 ===
许多事实上的分裂人格者能表现出迷人、精于社交的特点，与DSM-IV和ICD-10对分裂人格的定义描述的表面特征产生矛盾。<ref name=Klein>{{cite book |title=Disorders of the Self: Secret Pure Schizoid Cluster Disorder |year=1995|pages=25–27 |author=Masterson, James F.|author2=Klein, Ralph|quote=Klein was Clinical Director of the Masterson Institute and Assistant Professor of Psychiatry at the Columbia University College of Physicians and Surgeons, New York |authorlink=James F. Masterson}}</ref> Klein将这类人归为“隐秘的分裂人格者”<ref name=Klein />，外部表现为可交往、对人感兴趣、有参与精神和互动行为但保持感情上的孤僻，“隐居”在安全的内部世界里。

对外部世界的躲避或疏离是分裂病理学的典型特征，可能以“经典”（classic）或“隐秘”（secret）的形式出现。经典分裂人格与DSM-IV提供的分裂人格的描述相符，但由于客观外部观察往往无法与病人的主观内部世界匹配，它也常常作为一种隐秘的内部状态。Klein因此警示人们不应错过隐秘的分裂人格者：由于病人与外界现实的防御性、补偿性互动，人们往往无法观察到病人内心的挣扎。他提出察觉病人对亲密感的抗拒只需询问其主观感受。<ref name="Klein" />

“隐秘”分裂人格可以追溯到1940年Fairbairn对“分裂人格表现癖”的描述中：分裂人格者有能力表达大量情感并建立可观的社会联系，但在感情上既不付出也毫无损失。由于只是“扮演一个角色”，自己的人格并没有参与其中。“分裂者否认自己所扮演的角色而力图保留其人格完整，不作妥协。”<ref>[[罗纳德·费尔贝恩|Ronald Fairbairn]] (1952): ''Psychoanalytic Studies of the Personality''. pp 16–17.</ref>对“隐秘”分裂人格的更多描写来自于 {{tsl|en|Masud Khan||Masud Khan}},<ref name=":1">{{Cite book|title=The Privacy of the Self - Papers on Psychoanalytic Theory and Technique|last=Masud Khan|publisher=International Universities Press|year=1974|isbn=0823643107|location=New York|pages=70|chapter=The Role of phobic and counterphobic mechanisms and separation anxiety in schizoid character formation}}</ref> Jeffrey Seinfeld<ref name=":2">Jeffrey Seinfeld (1991): ''The Empty Core: An Object Relations Approach to Psychotherapy of the Schizoid Personality''. Jason Aronson, {{ISBN|0-87668-611-0}}.</ref> 他写道：“分裂人格者也希望参与社会活动、建立人际关系。但是，他们只是扮演一个角色，而不是全身心参与，自己并没有意识到自己已经拒绝了这个角色。”

{{link-en|Masud Khan|Masud Khan}}对隐秘分裂人格者作了进一步研究<ref name=":0">Masud Khan- 'The Role of phobic and counterphobic mechanisms and separation anxiety in schizoid character formation' in the volume 'The Privacy of the Self'. Here Khan remarks "...in the course of the treatment it became gradually clear that behind a façade of excessive sociability and [[wikt:venturesome|venturesomeness]] as well as random and frequent sexual episodes these patients had lived all their life... in a secretive and adamantly rejective state of withdrawal from all objects as well as from their environment." p. 70.</ref>；Jeffrey Seinfeld<ref>J. Seinfeld- 'The Empty Core'. Seinfeld writes: "The schizoid may also seem to be sociable and involved in relationships. However, he is frequently playing a role and not ‘fully’ involved, unconsciously disowning this role..." </ref>与Philip Manfield<ref>Philip Manfield- 'Split Self, Split Object'. Manfield writes: "Not all schizoids keep away from people. It is not people that schizoids avoid, but emotional intimacy, self disclosure, and emotions both positive and negative." p.207</ref>描述了一个明显具有分裂人格的人，“享受”定期公开演讲但在观众尝试与他进行情感交流时感到困难。<ref>Philip Manfield- 'Split Self, Split Object'. p. 207</ref> 这些例子暴露出单独依靠外部行为观察来评估某人精神状况的不足。

=== 逃避型依附模式 ===
分裂人格究竟作为一个完整的人格障碍还是一种[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Attachment_in_adults#Dismissive.E2.80.93avoidant 逃避型的依附模式] {{Wayback|url=http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Attachment_in_adults#Dismissive.E2.80.93avoidant |date=20210504070554 }}是受争议的。如果SPD仅为需要更大感情距离的依附模式，那么人们在社交中展示出的问题反应可能部分源于社会舆论的指责。迄今不同来源都证实SPD与逃避依附模式具有相同点，<ref>M. L. West & A. E. Sheldon-Keller- 'Patterns of Relating' p. 111-113.</ref>并留下研究者如何在未来的诊断手册或治疗过程中更好应对分裂人格者的问题。需要注意的区别是，分裂人格者不主动寻求社会交往仅出于兴趣缺乏，而逃避型依附模式渴望交往但害怕受拒。

=== 分裂人格者的幻想 ===
{{See also|Mind-wandering}}一种病态的对于幻想和[[内省法|内省法]]的依赖一般可以看做对社会的{{tsl|en|Narcissistic withdrawal||自恋性退却}}。因此，幻想就促成了''自我流放''，尽管这种幻想对于分裂人格来说，比逃避来得复杂的多。<ref name="Klein6">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=PytkjA3HNqQC|title=Disorders of the Self – The Masterson Approach|author1=James F. Masterson|author2=Ralph Klein|publisher=Brunner / Mazel|year=1995|isbn=9780876307861|location=New York|pages=25–27; pp. 54–55; pp. 95–143 (therapy)|authorlink=James F. Masterson}}</ref>{{rp|p. 64}}

想象是他们和世界联系、互动的方式。它是关系的替代，但是尽管如此，它还是过于理想化的、防御性的、补充的机制。这是仅通过自我实现的，它并不会受到和真实的人和事的情感联系的影响，例如危险、焦虑。<ref name="Klein6"/> Klein将它解释为自我为了和他人建立联系而做的挣扎。想象让人格分裂者认为他们和外界还有联系，他们和别人建立的关系还没有危机。<ref name="Klein6"/> Laing<ref name="Laing1960">{{cite book|title=The Divided Self: an Existential Study in Sanity and Madness|last=Ronald D. Laing|publisher=[[Penguin_Books|Penguin Books]]|year=1965|isbn=9780140207347|location=Harmondsworth, Middlesex; Baltimore|pages=82–100|chapter=The Inner Self in the Schizoid Condition|oclc=5212085|authorlink=R. D. Laing|chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4JT-12rMtJsC&pg=PT87}}</ref> 、Winnicott 和 Klein<ref name="Klein6"/>{{rp|p. 64}}对于人格分裂的这种视角做了详细阐述<ref>Donald Winnicott: Playing and Reality. Routledge Classics, 2012.  {{ISBN|9781135070939}}  pp. 26–38</ref>。

=== 分裂人格者的性行为 ===
分裂人格者通常较性冷淡，但却不一定患{{link-en|性感缺失病|Anorgasmia}}。对独处和疏离的偏好可能导致他们对性的要求表现得比非分裂人格者更少。与他人进行性行为通常使分裂人格者感到个人空间被侵犯，所以他们普遍感觉[[自慰|自慰]]或[[禁欲|禁欲]]比性行为时需忍受的亲密感更容易接受。<ref>Nannarello, J., Schizoid. Journal of Nervous Mental Diseases 1953</ref><ref>'Schizoid Phenomena, Object Relations, and the Self'</ref> 但也有值得注意的例外，有些分裂人格者可以与他人进行偶尔甚至经常的性行为。<ref>Nannarello, J., Schizoid. Journal of Nervous Mental Diseases 1953 p.240-242</ref><ref name=":3">{{Cite journal|last=Nannarello|first=Joseph J.|year=1953|title=Schizoid|url=http://journals.lww.com/jonmd/Citation/1953/09000/Schizoid.4.aspx|journal=The Journal of Nervous and Mental Disease|volume=118|issue=3|pages=237–249|pmid=13118367|doi=10.1097/00005053-195309000-00004|access-date=2017-10-06|archive-date=2021-05-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210525182112/https://journals.lww.com/jonmd/Citation/1953/09000/SCHIZOID.4.aspx|dead-url=no}}</ref>

Harry Guntrip<ref name=":4">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.de/books?id=NFthUnBVwNEC&printsec=frontcover&hl=de|title=Schizoid Phenomena, Object-Relations, and The Self|last=Harry Guntrip|publisher=International Universities Press|year=1969|isbn=9781855750326|location=New York|pages=|quote=|via=|access-date=2017-10-06|archive-date=2017-09-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170915114342/https://books.google.de/books?id=NFthUnBVwNEC&printsec=frontcover&hl=de|dead-url=no}}</ref>{{rp|p. 303}} 描述了一些婚后分裂人格者涉入的“秘密性关系”，作为一种减少单段感情所需亲密感的尝试。这种观点也和[[卡伦·霍妮|卡伦·霍妮]]的“放弃人格”（resigned personality）不谋而合，即患者可能认为“作为长期交往的性行为太亲密”，“转而同陌生人发生性关系以满足需要”，“将关系限制于单纯的性接触但不与伴侣分享其他经验。”<ref>{{Cite book|title=Neurosis and Human Growth: The Struggle Towards Self-Realization|last=Karen Horney|publisher=Routledge|year=1999|isbn=9780415210959|location=|pages=264–265|chapter=Resignation: The Appeal of Freedom|quote=|via=}}</ref>纽约大学社会福利工作教授Jeffrey Seinfeld，出版了一项对SPD的研究<ref>J. Seinfeld- The Empty Core: An Object Relations Approach to Psychotherapy of the Schizoid Personality' p. 104</ref>，详细描述了一种表现为[[性滥交|性滥交]]的“分裂者的饥渴”。他给出了一位分裂人格女士的例子：她会秘密出席各种酒吧结识男人以获得无感情参与的性满足来减轻她的饥渴和空虚。

Salman Akhtar更准确地描述了这种或公开或秘密的性行为的相互作用；他没有遵循将分裂人格者分为有性或[[無性戀|無性戀]]的狭隘的观点，提出尽管它们具有相反特点但可能同时存在于个人行为中<ref name="Akhtar">{{cite journal|year=1987|title=Schizoid Personality Disorder: A Synthesis of Developmental, Dynamic, and Descriptive Features|url=https://books.google.de/books?id=bU0eAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA121|journal=American Journal of Psychotherapy|volume=41|issue=|pages=499–518|pmid=3324773|via=|author=Salman Akhtar|access-date=2017-10-06|archive-date=2017-07-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170731160223/https://books.google.de/books?id=bU0eAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA121|dead-url=no}}</ref>。 对分裂人格者准确的临床描述因此必须包含表面特征：“无性恋、有时[[禁欲|禁欲]]、无感情兴趣、厌恶有关性的八卦和影射”与隐秘的行为：“偷窥和观看色情材料的兴趣、易受[[情愛妄想|情愛妄想]]的侵害、有[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Masturbation#Compulsive_masturbation 强迫手淫] {{Wayback|url=http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Masturbation#Compulsive_masturbation |date=20210526112733 }}和[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Perversion#Sexual_usages 变态] {{Wayback|url=http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Perversion#Sexual_usages |date=20210428221514 }}的倾向”，<ref name=Akhtar />尽管任一特点都不能适用于所有分裂人格者。

== 发病原因 ==
一些证据显示，A类人格障碍（奇怪型或異常型疾患）：[[妄想型人格違常|妄想型人格違常]]、[[類精神分裂型人格違常|類精神分裂型人格違常]]、[[分裂病型人格違常|分裂病型人格違常]])受一些相同的基因、环境因素影响。如果人有[[精神分裂症|精神分裂症]]或者[[分裂性人格障礙|分裂性人格障礙]]的话，他们有分裂人格障碍的危险也会增加。[[双生子研究|双生子研究]]表明，分裂人格障碍是遗传性的。除了这个直接证据，研究表明<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Kenneth S. Kendler|date=2006|year=|title=Dimensional representations of DSM-IV Cluster A personality disorders in a population-based sample of Norwegian twins: a multivariate study|url=https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Kristian_Tambs/publication/6894555_Dimensional_representations_of_DSM-IV_Cluster_A_personality_disorders_in_a_population-based_sample_of_Norwegian_twins_A_multivariate_study/links/0fcfd51223327b660c000000.pdf|journal=Psychological Medicine|volume=36|issue=11|pages=1583–1591|doi=10.1017/S0033291706008609|via=|pmid=16893481|access-date=2017-10-06|archive-date=2018-11-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181120095540/https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Kristian_Tambs/publication/6894555_Dimensional_representations_of_DSM-IV_Cluster_A_personality_disorders_in_a_population-based_sample_of_Norwegian_twins_A_multivariate_study/links/0fcfd51223327b660c000000.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Blaney2014">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=NQ0bBAAAQBAJ&pg=PA639|title=Oxford Textbook of Psychopathology|first=|date=2014|publisher=Oxford University Press|year=|isbn=978-0-19-981184-7|location=|pages=649|author1=Paul H. Blaney Ph.D.|access-date=2017-10-06|archive-date=2017-03-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170330122314/https://books.google.com/books?id=NQ0bBAAAQBAJ&pg=PA639|dead-url=no}}</ref> ，分裂人格的遗传率大约在50%-59%。参与这项研究的{{tsl|en|Sula Wolff||Sula Wolff}}表示，“人格分裂”是与生俱来的，很有可能是由基因控制的<ref name=":8">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.de/books?id=Oo9kWqaGqkoC&q=schizoid+personality+has+a+constitutional%2C+probably+genetic#v=snippet&|title=Loners - The Life Path of Unusual Children|first=|publisher=Routledge|year=1995|isbn=978-0-415-06665--5|location=|pages=35|last1=Sula Wolff|authorlink1=Sula Wolff|access-date=2017-10-06|archive-date=2017-09-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170915114057/https://books.google.de/books?id=Oo9kWqaGqkoC&q=schizoid+personality+has+a+constitutional%2C+probably+genetic#v=snippet&|dead-url=no}}</ref> ”。人格分裂和[[体重不足|体重不足]]也有可能有基因上的联系。<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Amber A. Mather|first=|year=2008|title=Associations Between Body Weight and Personality Disorders in a Nationally Representative Sample|journal=Psychosomatic Medicine|volume=70|issue=9|pages=1012–1019|doi=10.1097/psy.0b013e318189a930|via=|online=|pmid=18842749}}</ref><ref name="Millon 11">''[http://www.turkpsikiyatri.org/arsiv/personality.disorders.millon.pdf#388 The Schizoid Personality (Chapter 11).] {{Wayback|url=http://www.turkpsikiyatri.org/arsiv/personality.disorders.millon.pdf#388 |date=20201130100504 }}'' In: {{tsl|en|Theodore Millon||Theodore Millon}} (2004). ''Personality Disorders in Modern Life.'' Wiley, 2nd Edition. {{ISBN|0-471-23734-5}}. S. 371.</ref>

一般来说，产前孕妇[[營養不良|營養不良]], [[早產|早產]]以及出生时体重低下都有可能使新生儿遭受[[精神病|精神病]]的影响，同时也容易使他们发展成为分裂人格障碍者。那些遭遇过{{tsl|en|traumatic brain injury||创伤性脑损伤}}的人也有这种危险。<ref>{{cite journal|year=2010|title=Birth weight, schizophrenia, and adult mental disorder: is risk confined to the smallest babies?|journal=Archives of General Psychiatry|volume=67|issue=9|pages=923–930|doi=10.1001/archgenpsychiatry.2010.100|via=|last1=Kathryn M. Abel|first1=|pmid=20819986}}</ref><ref name="Martins2010">{{cite journal|year=2010|title=Schizoid personality disorder linked to unbearable and inescapable loneliness|url=https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Willem_Martens/publication/247919672_Schizoid_personality_disorder_linked_to_unbearable_and_inescapable_loneliness/links/54ad4a530cf2828b29fc3a56.pdf|journal=The European Journal of Psychiatry|volume=24|issue=1|pages=|doi=10.4321/S0213-61632010000100005|via=|last1=Willem H.J. Martens|first1=|access-date=2017-10-06|archive-date=2017-02-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202011937/https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Willem_Martens/publication/247919672_Schizoid_personality_disorder_linked_to_unbearable_and_inescapable_loneliness/links/54ad4a530cf2828b29fc3a56.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>Brigham Young University (2014): [http://news.byu.edu/news/head-injuries-can-make-children-loners Head injuries can make children loners.] {{Wayback|url=http://news.byu.edu/news/head-injuries-can-make-children-loners |date=20210117011641 }} For original study, see {{cite journal|doi=10.1097/HTR.0000000000000040 | volume=30 | title=Right Frontal Pole Cortical Thickness and Social Competence in Children With Chronic Traumatic Brain Injury | journal=Journal of Head Trauma Rehabilitation | pages=E24–E31}}</ref>

其他研究发现，极度[[完美主义|完美主义]],<ref>{{cite journal | title = The Schizoid Child | journal = {{tsl|en|American Journal of Orthopsychiatry||American Journal of Orthopsychiatry}} | date = April 1946 |author1=R.L. Jenkins |author2=S. Glickman | volume = 16 | issue = 2 | pages = 255–61|doi=10.1111/j.1939-0025.1946.tb05379.x }}</ref>的、充满负能量的父母也可能会使孩子有分裂人格障碍。

== 诊断标准 ==

=== DSM-5 ===
自成年期早期開始且呈現在各種場合中，一種廣泛的模式，疏離社會關係及在人際場合侷限地表達感情的，表現符合以下四項(或更多)：
* 不欲求也不享受親近關係，包括身為家庭的一員
* 幾乎總是選擇孤單的活動
* 若有，也很少對與他人有性經驗感興趣
* 若有，也很少有活動讓他感到樂趣
* 除一等親外，缺乏親近朋友或知己
* 對他人的讚美或指責顯得漠不關心
* 顯現感情（emotional）冷漠、疏離或平淡的情感

=== ICD-10 ===
根据[[ICD-10|ICD-10]]，确诊类精神分裂型人格违常首先需要满足[[Personality_disorder|人格障碍]]（F60）的基本条件。其次，必须满足以下至少四项：

* 极少能从活动中得到乐趣
* 感情冷淡，漠不关心
* 拙于表达正面或负面的感情
* 对于他人的表扬和批评无动于衷
* [[性冷淡|性冷淡]]
* 喜欢独处
* 过度沉迷于[[幻想_(心理学)|幻想]]和自我反省
* 没有或几乎没有亲密的朋友，且不渴望亲密关系
* 对[[社會規範|社会传统]]和[[風俗|习俗]]不屑一顾

===Guntrip 标准===
Ralph Klein认为下列标准可以用来描述类精神分裂型人格，该标准由{{Translink|en|Harry Guntrip|4=Harry Guntrip}}提出：
*[[内向|内向]]
*{{Internal link helper/en|离群|Withdrawnness}}
*[[自恋|自恋]]
*{{Translink|en|Self-sufficiency|4=自我满足感|自我满足感}}
*{{Translink|en|Grandiosity|4=优越感|优越感}}
*缺少[[情感_(心理學)|情感]]
*{{Translink|en|Loneliness|4=孤独感|孤独感}}
*[[人格解體|人格解體]]
*[[退行|退行]]
上述的九种特征阐明了传统[[DSM-5|DSM]]体系中对于SPD的描述与[[客体关系理论|客体关系理论]]之间的些许差异。所有的九个特征都具有一致性。在诊断类精神分裂障碍时，应满足上述的所有（或大多数）特征。<ref name=":0" />

您可以在关于{{tsl|en|Harry Guntrip|4=Harry Guntrip}}的文章中阅读更多细节。

=== 批评 ===

有人建议，人格分裂最好用两种精神疾病来代表。一种是“情感受限”（属于分裂性人格障碍），另一种是“自我封闭”（属于回避性人格障碍）。所以，有些人建议DSM删除这种类精神分裂性人格障碍，将它替换成维度模型。<ref name=":12">{{Cite journal|last=Skodol|date=2011|title=Personality Disorder Types Proposed for DSM-5|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/51019147|journal=Journal of Personality Disorders|volume=25|issue=2|pages=136–69|doi=10.1521/pedi.2011.25.2.136|pmid=21466247|quote=It [SPD] was found by [https://www.researchgate.net/publication/5775313_Dimensions_of_DSM-IV_Personality_Disorders_and_Life-Success Ulrich (2007)] to have the lowest functioning among the PDs with respect to achievement and interpersonal relations...|access-date=2020-11-05|archive-date=2021-08-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210829050156/https://www.researchgate.net/publication/51019147_Personality_Disorder_Types_Proposed_for_DSM-5|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 流行病學分析 ==
* 文化：來自不同文化背景的人有時會表現出防衛性行為及人際往來方式，而可能被誤認定屬於類分裂性
* 盛行率：低於2％，在臨床場所相當罕見。
* 性別：男性＞女性
* 年齡：若於兒童期及青春期出現，表現出與眾不同而常遭受嘲笑戲弄。

